Common.Highlight.Common.Text: The D'Arcy Arms Hotel and vacant land

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present to the market 2921 Gold Coast Highway and 30 Aubrey Street, Surfers Paradise. A high profile development site on the cusp of North Broadbeach and within the Northcliffe region of Surfers Paradise. 

This 3,154sqm* site is split into two equal sized parcels fronting the Gold Coast Highway and zoned High Density Residential.

The site is home to the Gold Coast's iconic Irish themed hotel, The DArcy Arms. The hotel is located on 2921 Gold Coast Highway and is currently an operating venue with seventeen motel rooms. The adjoining property at 30 Aubrey Street is currently leased to Pri Park, a car park management group. 

- 3,154sqm* development site 
- The DArcy Arms Hotel and vacant land
- High Density Residential zoning with no building height restrictions
- 250 metres* to the beach 
- Close to the Northcliffe Light Rail Station

The subject property is being offered for sale by Expressions of Interest, closing Wednesday, 6 October 2021 at 4pm.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: HIGH-RISE DEVELOPMENT SITE | Receivers & Managers Appointed

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Close to myriad of lifestyle amenities

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The Premiere, 71 Garfield Terrace, Surfers Paradise is a prime, direct beachfront development site which is improved by a significantly under-developed eight-storey, six-unit apartment building. 

71 Garfield Terrace offers 20 metres* of direct beach frontage and has a total land area of 865sqm*, and under the LAP for the suburb has no maximum restrictions on building height, therefore has the potential to be developed into a premium residential tower.

The existing eight-level The Premiere building situated on the site, consists of four full floor apartments, one two-level apartment, and a two storey penthouse, and additional rooftop pool with view terrace. On the ground floor there is basement parking, an outdoor swimming pool and barbecue terrace overlooking the beach. The existing improvements give the incoming purchaser a unique opportunity to either occupy themselves, or holiday rent, and enjoy a significant holding income, whilst approvals are being sought for the future development of the site. 

- Currently improved by under-developed eight-storey six-unit apartment building 
- 865 sqm site* with 20 metres* beach frontage 
- Ideally suited for premium residential tower
- Close to wide range of lifestyle amenity
